Glitch Setup: (==) Make your way to the Boko in front of Temple of Time and kill it. You can break one tree branch as long as you pick up the Boko Club. The important thing is to have 6 weapons at this point and then make sure none of them are equipped.
(==) Make sure to unequip all weapons before the next step.
(==) On the ground next to the chest, drop the peppers and flint.
(==) Wait for the autosave to trigger, then pick up the items dropped on the ground.
(==) After picking up the items, immediately make a manual hard save.
(==) After making the manual hard save, go into the Switch system settings, and set the clock to at least 1 day in the past. This will protect the SoR and ToT autosaves.
(==) Do not make any hard saves until the start of IST.
(==) Continue the route, but do not pick up bomb arrows or koroks until the doc indicates to do so.
(==) The doc will indicate the minimum number of any item that needs to be picked up.

Naydra Farming: (==) Move a bit northeast to the location indicated. Set time to morning while looking at the mountain top. Go quickly to N19.
(==) While doing N19, Naydra should be audible coming up the side of mountain. Move to the location indicated, then stand at the edge and wait. Hopefully the horn lands in the area aroud N19.

(==) Move down the side of the mountain and set a fire to morning. Naydra should be coming from the west over Lanayru Bay. Continue gliding NW toward N12, and look west down Lanayru Bay. Naydra should spawn. Shoot the claw when she gets near the N12 area. If the claw flies off in a bad location, get N12 first then chase the claw.
